correctness.rationale: Major factual and schema issues throughout. Key problems: (1) Units/values incorrect: pressure set to 133.3 with unit MilliM_HG (mmHg), but article reports ~1 Torr ≈ 1 mmHg (133.3 Pa); dosingTime entered as 50 ms while article states 1–50 s exposures; growthPerCycle set to 113 Å/cycle by misusing QCM mass uptake (113 ng cm^-2 cycle^-1) measured on a clean sensor, not thickness; filmThickness = 50 nm incorrectly taken from quantum-dot film thickness, not deposited ZnO film. (2) Unsupported or invented values: saturation = False, nucleationPeriod = 3 cycles, flowRates = 0.0 sccm, conformality.aspectRatio = 1.0, atomicRatio Zn:O = 1:1, uniformity.variation = 30% (this was shrinkage due to NH4OH, not uniformity), filmStability = True, reproducibility = True – none substantiated by the text. (3) Misplaced context: electricalProperties.mobility and deviceProperties.fieldEffectMobility set to 8.7 cm^2/V·s; article reports mobility of the QD film after ALD in the 10^-2–10^-1 cm^2/V·s range (e.g., 8.7×10^-3), not 8.7, and no TFT field-effect mobility is reported. (4) Numerous schema violations: many fields set to null (e.g., plasmaPower, growthPerCycle.filmThickness, supercycleDesign, thresholdVoltage, subthresholdSwing) where the schema expects objects; placeholders like "Not Found" used for required strings (carrierGas, purgingGas, deliveryMethod, etc.); zero values used as stand-ins (roughness, filmDensity, elementalConcentration) though not reported. (5) Incomplete/incorrect mapping: reactor/manufacturer unknown; only one of two ALD systems represented; QCM mass uptake trends described but not properly captured in schema-compliant terms. Overall, the extraction contains multiple incorrect values, unsupported assertions, and schema-type violations; several required fields are improperly populated. Properties to correct/review include: pressure (unit/value), dosing/purge times, growthPerCycle, filmThickness, mobility values and placement, uniformity, composition, flow rates, and removal of null/placeholder entries or replace with traceable values.

completeness.rationale: Major gaps and inaccuracies versus the article and multiple schema violations. Examples: (1) Multiple processes not captured: two distinct ALD systems (cold-walled quartz chamber and hot-walled stainless steel tube with QCM) and different cycle counts (3, 10, 15) are reported, but only one process is extracted. (2) Incorrect units/values: pressure set to 133.3 mmHg (should be ~1 mmHg ≈ 133.3 Pa); dosing/purge times entered as 50 ms while article reports 1–50 s; GPC set to 113 Å/cycle by misusing a mass uptake value (113 ng cm⁻² cycle⁻¹), which is not a thickness and is orders of magnitude too high. (3) Misattributed properties: filmThickness = 50 nm is for the QD film, not the deposited ZnO; refractive index n ≈ 2 and mobilities (8.7 cm² V⁻¹ s⁻¹) pertain to the composite QD films/devices, not intrinsic ZnO film properties; deviceProperties are for TFTs, but no TFTs are described. (4) Unsupported placeholders: carrierGas/purgingGas “Not Found”, flowRates set to 0.0, filmDensity/roughness = 0, atomicRatio 1:1, saturation=False, nucleationPeriod=3 cycles, conformality aspect ratio=1—none are grounded in the text. (5) Schema compliance issues: several fields are null (e.g., plasmaPower, supercycleDesign, thicknessControl.filmThickness), which violates required object types; thicknessControl structure and required fields are misused. To improve, add separate processes for each reactor/condition set; correct pressure and dosing times; remove invented values (0 or 1:1) and nulls; avoid using QD film properties as ZnO film properties; capture reported ranges (1–50 s, ~100 °C, ~1 Torr N₂ environment for measurements) and include only traceable parameters. Review and populate reactant carrier/purge gases if stated, and omit deviceProperties not applicable to TFTs.
